<div class="page-head"><h2>Tutorial · 2D Shooter</h2></div>

<DocsPage Slug="tutorial-2d-shooter">
    <h1>Build a 2D multiplayer arena shooter</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        A top-down free-for-all where players move, aim, and shoot each other in real time. Movement
        is replicated by the drop-in <a href="/dashboard/docs/sync-nodes">SpawnSync</a> node (smooth,
        no hand-written sync), shots travel over the event relay, and each player owns their own
        health — the full SpawnWeaver toolkit in one small game.
    </p>

    <p style="margin:10px 0">
        <span class="badge badge-cyan">Matchmaking</span>
        <span class="badge badge-cyan">SpawnSync</span>
        <span class="badge badge-cyan">Realtime events</span>
        <span class="badge badge-green">Damage &amp; respawn</span>
    </p>

    <div class="banner banner-warn">
        <span>📋</span>
        <span>First time? Do the <a href="/dashboard/docs/getting-started">Quickstart</a> — create a
            project, install the SDK, and save your public key in the <strong>SpawnWeaver dock</strong>.
            This tutorial uses <code>connect_using_config()</code>, which reads that saved key.</span>
    </div>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>SpawnSync owns movement.</strong> Each player is a small scene with a
            <strong>SpawnSync</strong> child. On the copy you control it streams your position,
            rotation, and <code>hp</code>; on copies of other players it <em>interpolates</em> toward
            their updates so they glide instead of teleporting. No <code>patch_entity_state</code> and
            no interpolation code in your game.</li>
        <li><strong>Shots are events.</strong> Firing sends a <code>shoot</code> event with a position
            + direction; every other client spawns that bullet locally.</li>
        <li><strong>You are authoritative over your own health.</strong> Each client only checks
            bullets against <em>its own</em> player and lowers its own <code>hp</code> — and because
            <code>hp</code> is a SpawnSync synced property, the new value replicates to everyone.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>1. The player scene</h2>
    <p>Make a new <strong>Node2D</strong> scene saved as <code>player.tscn</code>, and attach this
        script. It only <em>draws</em> — SpawnSync does the networking.</p>
    <pre>extends Node2D
## A player avatar. The SpawnSync child streams position, rotation, and hp — so this only draws.

var color := Color.WHITE
var hp: int = 100:
    set(value):
        hp = value
        queue_redraw()

func _draw() -> void:
    draw_circle(Vector2.ZERO, 16.0, color)                       # body
    draw_line(Vector2.ZERO, Vector2.RIGHT * 26.0, color, 4.0)    # barrel (node rotation aims it)
    var w := 36.0
    var top := Vector2(-w * 0.5, -30.0)
    draw_rect(Rect2(top, Vector2(w, 5.0)), Color(0, 0, 0, 0.5), true)
    draw_rect(Rect2(top, Vector2(w * clampf(float(hp) / 100.0, 0.0, 1.0), 5.0)), Color(0.56, 0.81, 0.43), true)</pre>
    <p>Now add the networking with <strong>one node</strong>: select the root, <em>Add Child Node</em>
        → <strong>SpawnSync</strong>, and in its Inspector set:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Transform:</strong> <em>Sync position</em> and <em>Sync rotation</em> on.</li>
        <li><strong>Custom properties → Synced properties:</strong> add one entry, <code>hp</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Sending → Send rate:</strong> <code>12</code> — a touch under the default so shoot
            events have rate-limit headroom (sending 20+ position updates/sec <em>and</em> shots can hit
            the limit and make remotes stutter).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Save the scene. That's the entire networking setup for a player.</p>

    <h2>2. The arena scene</h2>
    <p>Make a <strong>Node2D</strong> scene saved as <code>arena_2d.tscn</code>, set it as the main
        scene, and attach a new script. Paste each part below in order.</p>

    <h3>2a. Constants &amp; state</h3>
    <pre>extends Node2D
## 2D arena shooter (free-for-all). Movement/hp via SpawnSync; shots via the event relay.

const GAME_MODE := "arena2d_ffa"
const SPEED := 220.0
const BULLET_SPEED := 540.0
const FIRE_COOLDOWN := 0.22
const MAX_HP := 100
const HIT_DAMAGE := 25
const PLAYER_RADIUS := 16.0
const BULLET_RADIUS := 5.0
const ARENA := Rect2(40, 96, 880, 460)
const PlayerScene := preload("res://player.tscn")

var _status: Label
var _find_btn: Button

var _in_match := false
var _respawning := false
var _fire_cd := 0.0
var _me: Node2D = null
var _remotes: Dictionary = {}     # entity_id -> player Node2D
var _bullets: Array = []          # [{ owner, pos, vel, ttl }]</pre>

    <h3>2b. Connect &amp; subscribe</h3>
    <pre>func _ready() -> void:
    _build_ui()
    MultiplayerService.welcomed.connect(func(_id): _set_status("Connected. Click Find Match."))
    MultiplayerService.connection_error.connect(func(r): _set_status("Connection error: " + r))
    MultiplayerService.matchmaking_queued.connect(func(_m, _r, _s): _set_status("Searching for players…"))
    MultiplayerService.match_found.connect(_on_match_found)
    MultiplayerService.matchmaking_timeout.connect(func(_m, _r): _on_match_over("No match found — try again."))
    MultiplayerService.state_snapshot_received.connect(_on_snapshot)
    MultiplayerService.entity_state_changed.connect(func(id, _p, full): _ensure_remote(id, full))
    MultiplayerService.player_left.connect(func(_r, pid): _remove_remote(pid))
    MultiplayerService.event_received.connect(_on_event)</pre>

    <h3>2c. Spawn your player + a node per remote</h3>
    <p>When the server pairs you it fires <code>match_found</code>. You spawn your own player
        (<code>local = true</code> tells SpawnSync to send), and one player scene per other entity you
        hear about (SpawnSync interpolates those and frees them on leave).</p>
    <pre>func _on_match_found(_room_id: String, room_code: String, _players_list: Array) -> void:
    _in_match = true
    _respawning = false
    _bullets.clear()
    _spawn_local()
    _find_btn.disabled = true
    _set_status("Match %s! Arrows move · mouse aims · click/space shoots." % room_code)

func _spawn_local() -> void:
    if _me != null:
        return
    _me = PlayerScene.instantiate()
    _me.color = Color(0.96, 0.70, 0.36)
    _me.position = _random_spawn()
    _me.get_node("SpawnSync").local = true   # SpawnSync registers + streams my transform and hp
    add_child(_me)

func _ensure_remote(id: String, state: Dictionary) -> void:
    if id == MultiplayerService.player_id or _remotes.has(id):
        return
    var p := PlayerScene.instantiate()
    p.color = Color(0.91, 0.44, 0.29)
    if state.has("x") and state.has("y"):    # start where the entity already is (no slide-in)
        p.position = Vector2(float(state["x"]), float(state["y"]))
    if state.has("hp"):
        p.hp = int(state["hp"])
    p.get_node("SpawnSync").entity_id = id   # remote: interpolate this entity; auto-free on leave
    add_child(p)
    _remotes[id] = p

func _remove_remote(id: String) -> void:
    var p = _remotes.get(id, null)
    if p != null and is_instance_valid(p):
        p.queue_free()
    _remotes.erase(id)

func _on_snapshot(snapshot: Dictionary) -> void:
    for e in snapshot.get("entities", []):
        _ensure_remote(str(e.get("entityId", "")), e.get("state", {}))</pre>

    <h3>2d. Move your player — only when this window is focused</h3>
    <p>You move only <code>_me</code>; SpawnSync streams it. Note the <strong>focus guard</strong>:
        when you test with two windows on one PC they share the same physical mouse, so an unfocused
        instance would keep aiming at your cursor and look like it's spinning on its own. Gating input
        on <code>get_window().has_focus()</code> means only the window you've clicked drives its player.</p>
    <pre>func _process(delta: float) -> void:
    if not _in_match or _me == null:
        return
    _fire_cd = maxf(0.0, _fire_cd - delta)
    if not _respawning and get_window().has_focus():
        _handle_input(delta)
    _update_bullets(delta)
    queue_redraw()

func _handle_input(delta: float) -> void:
    var move := Input.get_vector("ui_left", "ui_right", "ui_up", "ui_down")
    if move != Vector2.ZERO:
        var pos := _me.position + move * SPEED * delta
        pos.x = clampf(pos.x, ARENA.position.x, ARENA.end.x)
        pos.y = clampf(pos.y, ARENA.position.y, ARENA.end.y)
        _me.position = pos
    _me.rotation = (_me.get_global_mouse_position() - _me.position).angle()
    if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_accept") or Input.is_mouse_button_pressed(MOUSE_BUTTON_LEFT):
        _try_fire()</pre>

    <h3>2e. Shoot &amp; take damage</h3>
    <p>Firing spawns a bullet locally and sends a <code>shoot</code> event so everyone else spawns the
        same bullet. Each client only resolves hits on <em>itself</em>; setting <code>_me.hp</code>
        replicates through SpawnSync.</p>
    <pre>func _try_fire() -> void:
    if _fire_cd > 0.0:
        return
    _fire_cd = FIRE_COOLDOWN
    var dir := Vector2.RIGHT.rotated(_me.rotation)
    var muzzle := _me.position + dir * (PLAYER_RADIUS + 6.0)
    _bullets.append({"owner": MultiplayerService.player_id, "pos": muzzle, "vel": dir * BULLET_SPEED, "ttl": 1.4})
    MultiplayerService.send_event("shoot", {"x": muzzle.x, "y": muzzle.y, "dx": dir.x, "dy": dir.y})

func _on_event(event: String, data: Dictionary, _from_id: String) -> void:
    if event == "shoot":
        var dir := Vector2(float(data.get("dx", 0.0)), float(data.get("dy", 0.0)))
        _bullets.append({
            "owner": _from_id,
            "pos": Vector2(float(data.get("x", 0.0)), float(data.get("y", 0.0))),
            "vel": dir * BULLET_SPEED,
            "ttl": 1.4,
        })

func _update_bullets(delta: float) -> void:
    var still_alive: Array = []
    for b in _bullets:
        b["pos"] += b["vel"] * delta
        b["ttl"] -= delta
        if b["ttl"] &lt;= 0.0 or not ARENA.grow(40.0).has_point(b["pos"]):
            continue
        if _me != null and not _respawning and b["owner"] != MultiplayerService.player_id \
                and b["pos"].distance_to(_me.position) &lt;= PLAYER_RADIUS + BULLET_RADIUS:
            _take_hit()
            continue
        still_alive.append(b)
    _bullets = still_alive

func _take_hit() -> void:
    _me.hp -= HIT_DAMAGE      # the hp setter redraws; SpawnSync replicates the new value
    if _me.hp &lt;= 0:
        _respawn()
    else:
        _set_status("Hit! HP %d" % _me.hp)

func _respawn() -> void:
    _respawning = true
    _set_status("You were fragged! Respawning…")
    await get_tree().create_timer(1.5).timeout
    _me.position = _random_spawn()
    _me.hp = MAX_HP
    _respawning = false
    _set_status("Fight! Arrows move · mouse aims · click/space shoots.")</pre>

    <h3>2f. Draw, UI &amp; helpers</h3>
    <p>The arena draws its background and the bullets; each player scene draws itself.</p>
    <pre>func _draw() -> void:
    draw_rect(ARENA, Color(0.10, 0.09, 0.07), true)
    draw_rect(ARENA, Color(0.42, 0.30, 0.18), false, 3.0)
    for b in _bullets:
        draw_circle(b["pos"], BULLET_RADIUS, Color(1.0, 0.95, 0.7))

func _on_match_over(reason: String) -> void:
    _in_match = false
    _find_btn.disabled = false
    _set_status(reason)

func _random_spawn() -> Vector2:
    return Vector2(randf_range(ARENA.position.x + 40.0, ARENA.end.x - 40.0),
        randf_range(ARENA.position.y + 40.0, ARENA.end.y - 40.0))

func _my_name() -> String:
    return "P%d" % (randi() % 1000)

func _build_ui() -> void:
    var bar := HBoxContainer.new()
    bar.position = Vector2(16, 16)
    bar.add_theme_constant_override("separation", 8)
    add_child(bar)
    var connect_btn := Button.new()
    connect_btn.text = "Connect"
    connect_btn.pressed.connect(_on_connect)
    bar.add_child(connect_btn)
    _find_btn = Button.new()
    _find_btn.text = "Find Match"
    _find_btn.disabled = true
    _find_btn.pressed.connect(_on_find)
    bar.add_child(_find_btn)
    _status = Label.new()
    _status.position = Vector2(16, 56)
    _status.text = "Click Connect (uses the key saved in the SpawnWeaver dock)."
    add_child(_status)

func _on_connect() -> void:
    if MultiplayerService.connect_using_config():
        _set_status("Connecting…")
        _find_btn.disabled = false
    else:
        _set_status("Save your public key in the SpawnWeaver dock first.")

func _on_find() -> void:
    if not MultiplayerService.is_connected_to_server():
        _set_status("Connect first.")
        return
    MultiplayerService.join_matchmaking(GAME_MODE, "", 2, _my_name())
    _find_btn.disabled = true
    _set_status("Searching for players…")

func _set_status(text: String) -> void:
    _status.text = text</pre>

    <h2>3. Play it with two windows</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>In Godot: <em>Debug → Run Multiple Instances</em>, set <strong>2</strong>.</li>
        <li>Run the scene. In <strong>both</strong> windows click <strong>Connect</strong>, then
            <strong>Find Match</strong> — the server pairs you into the same arena.</li>
        <li><strong>Click a window to focus it</strong>, then arrows move, mouse aims, click/space
            shoots. Only the focused window controls its player (that's the focus guard) — the other
            holds still until you click into it, but it still takes damage. Frag your opponent and watch
            its health bar drop; check live connections on the
            <a href="/dashboard/debugger">Debugger</a>.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="banner" style="border-color:var(--border);color:var(--steel)">
        <span>🖱️</span>
        <span>Two windows on one PC share one mouse and keyboard, so you can only drive one at a time.
            To truly play two independent players, run it on <strong>two machines</strong> (or with two
            people). Latency is dominated by distance to your server's region — pick a region near your
            players.</span>
    </div>
    <p class="muted">Want more than two players per arena? Raise the match size in
        <code>join_matchmaking(GAME_MODE, "", 2, …)</code> (e.g. <code>4</code>) — everyone in the room
        is spawned automatically.</p>

    <h2>Extend it</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Lobbies instead of matchmaking</strong> — let friends play by code with
            <code>create_lobby()</code> / <code>join_lobby()</code> (see
            <a href="/dashboard/docs/tutorial-lobby">Lobby + ready check</a>).</li>
        <li><strong>Persist stats</strong> — save total kills to player storage so they carry across
            sessions (see <a href="/dashboard/docs/tutorial-profile">Save a player profile</a>).</li>
        <li><strong>More synced state</strong> — add fields like <code>team</code> or <code>name</code>
            to the SpawnSync <em>Synced properties</em> list and they replicate automatically.</li>
    </ul>

